# 🚀 PHASE 3: ADVANCED DATABASE DESIGN (ENTERPRISE EXTENSION)

---

## 🎯 PURPOSE

This phase enhances the system to support:

* Advanced business workflows
* Audit & tracking
* Scalability for large operations
* Better internal communication
* Enterprise-level control

---

# 🆕 NEW TABLES INTRODUCED

---

## 📌 1. leads

### 🔹 Purpose:

Track customer intent before vehicle creation.

### 🔹 Why Needed:

Currently system directly creates vehicles → no pre-tracking.

### 🔹 Structure:

* id (PK)
* customer_id (FK)
* created_by (Sales Executive)
* vehicle_id (FK, nullable)
* status (NEW, INSPECTION, APPROVED, REJECTED)
* created_at

---

## 📌 2. credit_notes

### 🔹 Purpose:

Handle exchange vehicle financial adjustments.

### 🔹 Why Needed:

Credit should not be stored directly in vehicles.

### 🔹 Structure:

* id (PK)
* valuation_id (FK)
* amount
* generated_date

---

## 📌 3. vehicle_sales

### 🔹 Purpose:

Track resale of inventory vehicles.

### 🔹 Why Needed:

Core revenue module of the system.

### 🔹 Structure:

* id (PK)
* vehicle_id (FK)
* buyer_id (FK)
* sale_price
* profit_margin
* sale_date

---

## 📌 4. vehicle_reconditioning

### 🔹 Purpose:

Track repair and refurbishment before resale.

### 🔹 Why Needed:

Used vehicles often require improvements before selling.

### 🔹 Structure:

* id (PK)
* vehicle_id (FK)
* work_done
* cost
* status (PENDING, COMPLETED)

---

## 📌 5. rc_transfer_tracking

### 🔹 Purpose:

Track RC ownership transfer process.

### 🔹 Why Needed:

Legal compliance + post-sale tracking.

### 🔹 Structure:

* id (PK)
* vehicle_id (FK)
* status (PENDING, IN_PROGRESS, COMPLETED)
* updated_at

---

## 📌 6. vehicle_notes ⭐

### 🔹 Purpose:

Store internal remarks across lifecycle.

### 🔹 Why Needed:

Critical for:

* Inspection comments
* Manager decisions
* Audit clarity

### 🔹 Structure:

* id (PK)
* vehicle_id (FK)
* user_id (FK)
* note
* created_at

